    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "How sad it is that many parents have cast off their God-given responsibility to their children, and are willing that strangers should bear it for them! They are willing that others should labor for their children and relieve them of all burden in the matter.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">3<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 10-25-1892\" data-link=\"821.12255\">The Review and Herald, October 25, 1892</span>.</span></a></sup>",
    "puborder": 549,
