    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 187.4 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Many who are now bemoaning the waywardness of their children have only themselves to blame. Let these look to their Bibles and see what God enjoins upon them as parents and guardians. Let them take up their long-neglected duties. They need to humble themselves and to repent before God for their neglect to follow His directions in the training of their children. They need to change their own course of action and to follow the Bible strictly and carefully as their guide and counselor.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Ms 57, 1897\" data-link=\"14062.6345001\">Manuscript 57, 1897</span>.</span></a></sup>",
